task.summary: Added test classes for more clear idea of how hiarchy in Intellij works vs Netbeans for George+Neethan
Added example on how to use DataPull api as a library. This example gets the temperature of two cities, compares them, and outputs a description.
The beginnings of the Observer pattern. Interfaces for the subject and observers, as well as class to store observers in an array list.
Pretty much implemented. Havent tested with main. Will do so, and revert main afterwards if it functions.
Made the MainObs class to run everything

Actually fixed DataPull by converting any long values to double, if there are any. Did this by adding a toDouble function. Next step is to add error checking for user inputted names (i.e names with spaces, and names of cities that aren't in API database)

FULLY error trapped DataPull. This accounts for: - not found cities - no input - spaces in input - undefined values returned from api (will return 0)
User can no longer crash the program from text box.
Updated the UI, included pictures for all pre-set cities. Also included a Toronto background photo for all stages, and different font colors for different attributes.

Finished Observer module and UI. Observer module has random changes since the API updates hourly, which takes too long. I use an algorithm to calculate random change for every single component the observer tracks.

Finished Observer module and UI. Observer module has random changes since the API updates hourly, which takes too long. I use an algorithm to calculate random change for every single component the observer tracks.

Added the netbeans project zip file, so we can run it on netbeans. Note: There was no straight up import export, so I had to make a new project, c+p all javafiles, and add library manually. Updates to main will not be pushed to the netbeans project. All changes will have to be pushed to the netbeans project manually.
